reviews.text: This is our favorite local Mexican restaurant and it never disappoints! We mostly get the Mocajete (with its delicious sauce and shrimp and chicken and steak all wrapped in a warm tortilla with beans and avocado, yum) but we also love the egg burritos, birria tacos con queso, and the fried steak with avocado. Mmm!

First time being here. When I got there it was about 3:00 p.m. was not very busy. But the staff was very friendly. I was seated quickly and they took my order. Didn't wait long for my order. I had the chicken enchilada plate, comes with refried beans but you can get other types of beans, and Spanish rice. It also came with tomato soup. I got chips and salsa they're free if you have a meal over $10 anything under you have to pay. The atmosphere was real pleasant. They had TVs and you can help yourself to the fountain drinks. Food was good. I will go back and try something else on the menu. Definitely well return.

Came here for the first time the other day and the food was amazing! However, I do need to note that I felt like our waitress provided sub-par service. I got the carnitas enchiladas with the red enchilada sauce. The rice was also some of the better rice I‚Äôve had from a sit down Mexican restaurant. I would also rate the chips and salsa in my top 3, just be sure you like some heat! I‚Äôd definitely come back to try their birria or just get the enchiladas again. If you haven‚Äôt been here yet you definitely need to try it! There‚Äôs a reason they‚Äôve been in business for so long.

My husband and I came here last week and it was great!! The food was delicious (I forgot to take picture before it but this is what it looks like it when food is yummy and you just want to devour it :) The service was fast (we got seated pretty quick ). Belen was our waitress and she was patient and friendly. We will definitely be coming back!!
Also if you haven‚Äôt tried the frozen horchatas, you guys should! Its delicious!!

We come here all the time for the birria street tacos! They are amazing. Their beans and rice are delicious and flavorful. The salsa actually has spice to it and the chips come out warm. We went today the day before Mother‚Äôs Day and the owners son was giving all the moms roses for Mother‚Äôs Day. It was so sweet! It‚Äôs small, family owned and authentic Mexican food. You won‚Äôt be disappointed, give it a try!

detailedReviews.author: Chris Smith
detailedReviews.text:
So the service was OK and the ambiance in the restaurant was nice. Unfortunately, neither of those can overcome the quality of the food. I was there with my wife, daughter and grandson as well as my daughter's mother-in-law and sisters-in-law. My daughter's in-laws had eaten here before and liked it, which is why we opted to eat there.

The presentation of the food was nice. It actually looked appetizing but when we started eating it, the experience went south pretty quickly. It just honestly tasted bad. It was not good at all. The molcajete was around $35 but it really didn't have $35 worth of food in it. Additionally, they used chicken thighs rather than breasts, which are cheaper, fattier and greasier than white meat. I ate about three bites and wrote the whole thing off. It was just gross and the flavors were way off. Even the salsa tasted wrong. I was told that my kid's mother in law actually complained to the staff about it but I wasn't there for it. I had to go out and reposition car seats for my grandson. I would have sent it all back but my wife didn't want to make a scene. To sum it up, it was awful, no one liked it and none of us will ever eat there again. The most irritating part of this kind of experience is that I had to drive out of my way for it and pay for it

On our fries there was even cooked pineapple in the topping which it didn‚Äôt say that it had it at all on the menu. The taste would‚Äôve been decent had it even been warm. The fries weren‚Äôt crispy at all and were very Soggy. Enchiladas didn‚Äôt even have the cheese melted on the top but a pile of cold cheese on the top of the plate. Won‚Äôt be returning. Very disappointed. They charge for a refill on chips and salsa.
